###
### jEdit hints
### By Slava Pestov <sp@gjt.org>
###

tip.0=These tips can be disabled in the Tools->Global Options dialog
tip.1=Press C+d C+d to delete the current line
tip.2=Press C+d C+s to delete from the start of the current line to the caret
tip.3=Press C+d C+f to delete from the caret to the end of the current line
tip.4=Try File->Open URL to fetch files via ftp & http
tip.5=The last 25 pasted strings are listed in the Edit->Paste Previous dialog
tip.6=The Buffers menu displays (modified) next to files that have changed
tip.7=Try File->Send to send the current file via e-mail
tip.8=Try Tools->Open in WWW Browser when editing an HTML file
tip.9=jEdit performs syntax colorizing when printing, too
tip.10=Try disabling Current Line Highlighting to speed jEdit up a bit
tip.11=Try disabling Syntax Colorizing to speed jEdit up a bit
tip.12=The -nosplash command line switch makes jEdit start a little faster
tip.13=When editing TeX files, Tools->Compile invokes amstex/latex for you
tip.14=The Escape key does the equivalent of pushing Cancel in a dialog
tip.15=The Enter key does the equivalent of pushing OK in a dialog
tip.16=Tab and Shift+Tab shift to the next and previous element in a dialog
tip.17=Give the Search->HyperSearch command a go sometime
tip.18=Press C+t to save the current position, and C+y to go back to it later
tip.19=C+LEFT and C+RIGHT move to the previous and next word, respectively
tip.20=C+UP and C+DOWN move to the next or previous paragraph
tip.21=Pressing Shift with an arrow key extends the selection in that direction
tip.22=A+LEFT and A+RIGHT shift a block of text left or right by one Tab
tip.23=Use markers to move around large documents
tip.24=The Open URL command isn't just for URLs: file names can be entered too
tip.25=The Save To URL command isn't just for URLs: file names can be entered too
tip.26=Try Edit->Format Text to make text look "nicer"
tip.27=C+x, C+c and C+v work in all text fields, not just the main editor
tip.28=jEdit home page: <http://www.gjt.org/~sp/jedit.html>
tip.29=Somelongword... Som<C+b> -> Somelongword... Try C+b sometime
tip.30=If the caret is after a bracket, C+] will go to the matching one
tip.31=C+[ selects the current code block ( { ... } )
tip.32=Send mail to Slava Pestov <sp@gjt.org> if you like jEdit
tip.33=Press F10 and use the arrow keys for mouse-free menu operation
tip.34=If you have additional hints, e-mail Slava Pestov <sp@gjt.org>
tip.35=Undo and Redo remember the last 100 editing actions
tip.36=Try Edit->Tabs to Spaces if you do not like using Tabs
tip.37=Try Edit->Spaces to Tabs if someone sent you a file with soft tabs
tip.38=Unix users: jEdit can transparently edit GZipped files
tip.39=Power users: edit jedit_gui.props to change the menu bar
tip.40=You can change menu item shortcuts in Tools->Global Options->Shortcuts
tip.41=Sysops: edit jedit.props to change site-wide settings
tip.42=jEdit is Open Source: give copies to your friends
tip.43=jEdit is Open Source: you can edit the source code to suit your needs
tip.44=Files can be opened read only for browsing with the -readonly switch
tip.45=When started with no parameters, jEdit opens files from the last session
tip.46=Menus and menu items can be selected with A+<underlined char>
tip.47=Markers are saved across editing sessions to .<filename>.marks
tip.48=If jEdit crashes, look in #<filename># for autosaved data
tip.49=When saving, jEdit first backs the file up to <filename>~
tip.50=Use File->New View to create a new editor window
tip.51=Auto indent coolness: press Tab on an indented line to insert a real Tab
tip.52=When editing HTML files, use File->Open Selection to check links
tip.53=To select lots of text, press C+t at the start and C+u at the end
tip.54=Press F7 to hide or show the console
tip.55=You can have more than one view editing a buffer (File->New View)
tip.56=Press F1 for help
tip.57=The window size is saved between editing sessions
tip.58=If menus act funny on Linux, upgrade to at least JDK 1.1.7
tip.59=File->Open Recent contains up to 8 previously opened file names
tip.60=jEdit can be customized to your needs in the Tools->Global Options dialog
tip.61=VI users: Edit->Paste Previous is a sort-of substitute for VI registers
tip.62=Mac users: jEdit uses Mac-style shortcuts: C+z, C+x, C+c, C+v, etc
tip.63=Windows users: try selecting the Windows L&F in the Options dialog
tip.64=CDE/Motif users: try selecting the Motif L&F in the Options dialog
tip.65=Mac users: try selecting the MacOS L&F in the Options dialog
tip.66=Unix users: To GZip the current file, do a Save As to <filename>.gz
tip.67=HTML mode colorizes JavaScripts in <script> tags - try it!
tip.68=If jEdit crashes during an autosave, you can still recover your file
tip.69=Press C+e C+j to center the current line on the screen
tip.70=Press C+e C+i to select the current line without any leading indent
tip.71=C+t saves the current position, C+e C+x flips between it and the caret
tip.72=Emacs users: the anchor works like the Emacs "mark"
tip.73=C+i will go to the first non-whitespace character of the current line
tip.74=If you prefer soft tabs, specify so in the Options dialog
tip.75=Try out the commenting commands in Edit->Code Block Operations
tip.76=F8 goes to the previous compiler error, F9 to the next
tip.77=Click on an error in the `Errors' tab of the console to go to it
tip.78=Regexp coolness: $1-$9 inserts the contents of subexpression 1-9
tip.79=Use UP/DOWN to recall the last 25 search & replace strings
tip.80=Use Edit->Paste Predefined to insert frequently used strings
tip.81=Jikes users: try `jikes +E' for jEdit to parse the errors
tip.82=Try File->Save All Buffers to save all open files
tip.83=A block caret can be enabled in Tools->Global Options->Editor
tip.84=Use File->Reload to reload the current file from disk
tip.85=Try right clicking on the text area
tip.86=There is a `Keep Dialog' option in Search & Replace
tip.87=The tool bar can be disabled in Tools->Global Options->General
tip.88=Quoted literals that don't end on the same line are shown differently
tip.89=HTML entities that don't end on the same line are shown differently
tip.90=The tab size can be set on a buffer-specific basis in Tools->Buffer Options
tip.91=C+e C+[ and C+e C+] open the previous and next buffer, respectively
tip.92=Try entering URLs in the console to open them
tip.93=The Tools->Buffer Options dialog sets properties on a per-buffer basis
tip.94=If you prefer Indent on Enter, enable it in Tools->Global Options->Editor
tip.95=It is possible to send the selection only in File->Send
tip.96=The help viewer can be used as a simple WWW browser
tip.97=For information about installed plugins, see Help->Plugin Help Contents
tip.98=You can change the default edit mode in Tools->Global Options->Editor
tip.99=Check out the jEdit plugin page <http://www.icg-online.de/jedit/>
tip.100=Pressing Insert toggles overwrite mode
tip.101=Use UP/DOWN to recall the last 25 console commands
tip.102=Check out Help->Help Contents->Advanced Text Editing->History Text Fields
tip.103=When editing an HTML file, press F10 to open it in your WWW browser
